  "title": "Product Marketing Manager, APAC (Contract)",
  "description": "<p><strong>This is a contract role ending in early February 2027.</strong><br /></p><p>The Marketing Manager leads product marketing strategy to drive product adoption, engagement, and growth across markets. This role translates market and user insights into clear positioning, go-to-market plans, and scalable marketing initiatives, partnering closely with product, regional, and cross-functional teams.<br /></p><p><strong>Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li><strong>Lead go-to-market planning and execution for new products and features, including launches and growth initiatives.</strong></li><li>Serve as the subject matter expert for assigned products or features, providing market analysis, competitive insights, and industry trend perspectives.</li><li>Define product positioning, value propositions, and messaging for different audiences and markets.</li><li>Develop and execute cross-channel marketing strategies, content frameworks, and medium- to large-scale campaigns.</li><li>Identify, track, and analyze key product and marketing metrics to evaluate market opportunity and campaign performance.</li><li>Incorporate user insights and research into product development, marketing strategy, and user experience improvements.</li><li>Partner with cross-functional teams to plan priorities, align stakeholders, and ensure consistent execution across regions.</li></ul><p><strong>Requirements</strong></p><ul><li><strong>7+ years of experience in product marketing or a closely related marketing role.</strong></li><li>Proven ability to lead multi-market initiatives, aligning regional needs with global product roadmaps.</li><li>Experience managing end-to-end growth experiments, coordinating execution across local and central teams.</li><li>Strong background in marketing planning and operations, including budget consolidation and goal-setting support.</li><li>Excellent cross-functional and stakeholder management skills, with the ability to influence senior leaders across regions and time zones.</li><li>Hands-on knowledge of lifecycle marketing, including retention, churn prevention, and CRM tools.</li></ul>",
